reviewText: WHAT A GREAT MOVIE WHY DONT THEY MAKE THEM LIKE THIS ANY MORE I KNOW PEOPLE LOVE THEM AND WOULD BUY THEM

My wife and I enjoyed the movie very much. We always review movies before we show them to our grand children. This is watchable and enjoyable for the whole family. You don't have to worry about inappropriate language or overt love scenes.
Excellent movie of living in the wilderness. Dealing with the challenges and dangers of this type of living was entertaining.
I had this on VCR and got this for my nephews and niece in the DVD version. Wholesome family fun and lessons on the beauty and power of nature. Shows self-reliance and the importance of family.
Love the movie very much. I didn't know it continues on until I spotted the number 2.
Yes it did!  My grandchildren love this series.
great film recommend to all family's with kids great full of nature and animals and no bad language
this is the second movie of the wilderness families adventure.  it is a good family film that shows how a city family that moves to the wilderness survives.  good film for the whole family.
